(1). Cross border trade, which is defined as delivery of a service from the territory of one country into the territory of other country;
(2) Consumption abroad - this mode covers supply of a service of one country to the service consumer of any other country;
(3) Commercial presence - which covers services provided by a service supplier of one country in the territory of any other country, and
(4) Presence of natural persons - which covers services provided by a service supplier of one country through the presence of natural persons in the territory of any other country.
